n ↔ edge node sync, cache invalidation, load balancing logic |\n\n## Recommended structure\n\n```\ntwitch-desent/           ← Open source (MIT or AGPL)\n├── cmd/server/\n├── internal/            ← All current packages\n├── web/\n├── Dockerfile\n└── ...\n\ntwitch-desent-cloud/     ← Closed source (private repo)\n├── discovery/           ← Server catalog + moderation\n├── antibot/             ← Bot detection, rate limiting heuristics\n├── installer/           ← Managed deployment orchestration\n├── edge/                ← CDN node coordination\n└── moderation/          ← Content moderation pipeline\n```\n\n## The strategic logic\n\n**Open the commodity, close the moat.** The streaming server itself is commodity tech (FFmpeg + HLS + WebSocket). Your competitive advantages are:\n\n1. **Ease of deployment** (installer app) — closed\n2. **Network effects** (discovery catalog) — closed\n3. **Trust & safety** (moderation + anti-bot) — closed\n4. **Managed hosting** (the paid product) — closed\n\nThis is the same model as GitLab (open core), Supabase (open server, closed cloud features), and Bitwarden (open client, proprietary enterprise features).\n\nWant me to help set up the repo structure for this split, or draft a LICENSE file?",
